Governor Greg Abbott today announced the opening of several hurricane evacuation centers across Texas, including one location in Ellis County at the Knights of Columbus Hall - 850 S Interstate Highway 45, Ennis TX.

In coordination with the Texas Division of Emergency Management, Ellis County Office of Emergency Management, the City of Ennis, The City of Midlothian, and the Knights of Columbus, this facility will serve as a reception center for those self-evacuating from Hurricane Laura. Texans passing through will be provided with information regarding FEMA, State, and non-profit resources. Additional information includes pet sheltering, lodging accommodations, and guidance regarding nearby hurricane shelters in the DFW Metroplex.

shared_text:
Jack Lummus Intermediate School
August 20 at 8:59 PM Â·

History was made today with the first day of school being virtual. While this did not bring any students physically into classrooms today, it was so good to see them on their Google Meets with their teachers, introducing themselves and catching up with each other. Another day-maker was seeing the lengths that parents are going to in order to make sure their children are online and ready to learn. We saw it all day today...the endless phone calls coming in to the front office, the concerned emails sent to teachers, the parents dropping by with chromebooks that were not cooperating at home, and families like this one who chose to do school at the shady picnic tables outside of Lummus in order to access the district internet. Thank you for your commitment to your children!

As educators, we were reminded today of our â€œwhyâ€. We long to be the calm in this PASSING storm of uncertainty for our students and parents, show compassion to our students along the way, and provide the best learning opportunities we can as we embark on the 2020-2021 school year.

#allENNIStogether

REMINDER: Please make sure that your children are enrolled and registered for the upcoming school year.

NEW TO ENNIS ISD? The enrollment process is for those children new to the district. If you are new to EISD, follow this link for more information on how to enroll your child.
https://www.ennis.k12.tx.us/Domain/4830

RETURNING STUDENT? Registration is for you. This will allow you to update all of your information in the system and submit any required forms. This online process replaces all of the paper forms you used to have to fill out at the first of school every year. Follow the link below for a detailed guide to student registration.
https://www.ennis.k12.tx.us/Page/6477

IMPORTANT NOTE: If you have signed your child up for the Virtual Learning Option, this DOES NOT take the place of enrollment or registration. Students still need to be enrolled or registered prior to school beginning on August 20th.

For any questions regarding the online enrollment and registration process, please email familyaccess@ennis.k12.tx.us

NEW TO ENNIS ISD? The enrollment process is for those children new to the district. If you are new to EISD, follow this link for more information on how to enroll your child.
https://www.ennis.k12.tx.us/Domain/4830

RETURNING STUDENT? Registration is for you. This will allow you to update all of your information in the system and submit any required forms. This online process replaces all of the paper forms you used to have to fill out at the first of school every year. Follow the link below for a detailed guide to student registration.
https://www.ennis.k12.tx.us/Page/6477

IMPORTANT NOTE: If you have signed your child up for the Virtual Learning Option, this DOES NOT take the place of enrollment or registration. Students still need to be enrolled or registered prior to school beginning on August 20th.

For any questions regarding the online enrollment and registration process, please email familyaccess@ennis.k12.tx.us

post_text: Congratulations to Madison Hamm.
shared_text:
Ennis FFA
July 6 at 2:33 PM Â·

This week a group of Ennis FFA Members and the 4 Advisors should be traveling to Dallas for the 92nd Texas FFA State Convention. However, due to COVID-19 convention has been moved to a virtual setting. This means our Lone Star recipient will be missing out on walking the stage to receive this great honor.

The Lonestar FFA Degree is the highest degree an FFA member can receive at the state level. To receive the Lone Star Degree a member must have been an active FFA member for at least two years, complete at least four semesters of agricultural science at or above the ninth grade level, maintain a supervised agricultural experience (SAE) program, invest significant time and money in their SAE, demonstrate their leadership skills and show a commitment to the FFA through involvement at the chapter level and above.

If you happen to see Madison (Maddie) this week, please congratulate her on this big accomplishment!

Ennis Independent School District
May 23 at 1:12 PM Â·

The Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text:
The Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

post_text:
Lion Nation,

As you may have heard, Governor Greg Abbott has now ordered all Texas schools closed for the remainder of this academic year. Although this continues to be a difficult time, we will continue to support our students to the best of our ability moving forward.

As he stated, the Texas Education Agency will be releasing more details soon about how this announcement will affect our students, families, and staff. As soon as this information is known, we will share it with you.

With this said, we will continue to provide our students with distance learning activities, free meals, and counseling services for the remainder of the school year.

We understand that this is a difficult time for our families and our entire community, but rest assured that Ennis ISD will be there every step of the way.

We Are Ennis!

Whether itâ€™s a cup of coffee, reconnecting with a friend you havenâ€™t talked to you in a while, spending time with family, or finding new hobbies at home that you didnâ€™t think you had time for in the past. This is a trying time for all of us across the country, but itâ€™s time for us all to find our own wellness. Enjoy the time with your families, take time to make time for yourself, find a time to exercise, find the time to read, and find that time just to let go. Weâ€™re all going to come out stronger from this in the end. So hereâ€™s to everyone, â€œBe Well....â€.
#WeAreEnnis

post_text:
Update:
Sunday, March 15th - 6:30pm

Lion Nation,

After meeting this afternoon and participating in our third conference call with the Commissioner of Education, we continue to make plans for serving our students in the most effective and safest platform possible. New information is coming forward daily.

Our staff is working diligently on an operational plan to provide meals for our students. The goal is to begin meal distribution no later than Wednesday of this week. Details concerning locations and times will be communicated tomorrow.

According to state officials, the school closure may be only a week, however, there is a possibility of many weeks if the pandemic continues to spread. In the event the closure is extended, we will provide educational resources through online and hard copy platforms. More information regarding these learning opportunities will be provided once there is a determination on the closure status.

We will share more information tomorrow as we move forward. Thank you for your patience and support.

Today is the last day to RSVP for Parenting Late Talkers, presented by Darla Gardner, MS, CCC-SLP (ASHA Certified Speech Language Pathologist and Hanen Certified Speech Language Pathologist)! Join us this Thursday, February 6th, to learn how to teach your child critical language skills through daily routines and play.

While the target audience for this seminar is parents with children ages newborn to 7 years old, all parents are welcome to attend. This seminar is FREE to all Ennis ISD parents and guardians. Pizza will be provided for all attendees, and childcare is available for ages 3+.

RSVP to Dusty Laurence at dusty.laurence@ennis.k12.tx.us by Monday, February 3rd. Contact Darla Gardner with questions regarding the seminar at darla.gardner@ennis.k12.tx.us.

Toys and gifts from the Salvation Army were delivered to the First United Methodist Church this week for distribution to families who signed up for Christmas assistance earlier this fall.

As a result of countless donations, over 100 children will receive toys and clothes. EISD administrators assisted in the unloading of the boxes and sacks that will be distributed to families for the holiday. Thanks to everyone who assisted in this effort.

REMINDER: Today will be an early release day for all grade levels due to Winter Break. The early release schedule is as follows:

Carver and Crockett ECC will dismiss at 11:45am.
Austin, Bowie, Houston, and Travis will dismiss at 11:55am.
Lummus and Miller will dismiss at 12:05pm.
Junior High and High School will dismiss at 12:35pm, with sack lunches available until 1:00pm for students who wish to pick one up. Buses for EJHS and EHS will begin running at approximately 12:45pm.

Students will return to school Tuesday, January 7th. Have a great winter break!

post_text:
Join the Ennis Choral Department for "Christmas Time in the City" at the Family Life Center at Tabernacle Baptist Church tomorrow night! This dinner concert will feature Christmas songs performed by students in the Ennis Junior High and Ennis High school choirs, with a silent auction and raffle tickets available for purchase throughout the night! Tickets are $15 for adults and $10 for ages 3-10 (children 3 and under eat free).

Doors open at 5:30pm with music and food starting at 6pm. Come out and celebrate the season while supporting the Ennis Choral Department!!
shared_text:
Ennis Choral Department
December 13, 2019 at 10:00 AM Â·

We are very excited for the concert tomorrow night! Come out and see "Christmas Time in the City" tomorrow night in the family life center at Tabernacle Baptist Church. Doors open at 5:30 p.m., Music and food starts at 6:00 p.m.. (Choir students arrive at 2:15 to rehearse.)

Tickets are $15 for adults, $10 for 10 and under, and 3 and under eat free. Each ticket includes a full turkey dinner!

This event serves as a concert and a fundraiser. A silent auction will be held, as well as raffle tickets for custom furniture from EB construction.

We hope to see you tomorrow!

Ennis High School senior Stoney Duke was recently selected to the Academic All-State 2nd team by the Texas High School Coaches Association! To be selected for an Academic All-State team, a student athlete must be a senior of good moral character and have a cumulative average of 92 or high for their entire high school career.

Congratulations on this accomplishment, Stoney! Go Lions!

Although we are not expecting any closures or delays with the falling temperatures, in the event of winter weather closures or delays, Ennis ISD will use these methods of communication to notify the public. Keep in mind, we only contact you if there is a change to the normal district schedule.

In addition to these outlets, we will also call, text, and email students and parents to notify them accordingly. Now would be a great time to log into Skyward Family Access to be sure your phone numbers and emails are up-to-date. For any questions about Family Access, please send an email to familyaccess@ennis.k12.tx.us.

The Ennis Lions take on Aledo TONIGHT at the State Quarterfinal Playoff game at The Star in Frisco! Tickets can be purchased through the link below or at the gate tonight for $15. The ticket office at The Star will be open beginning at 5:30pm, and the stadium doors will open at 6pm.

The only pass accepted for admission this week will be the THSCA coaches pass. Everyone age 1 and up will need a ticket for this week's game. If you are purchasing your tickets online, it does not matter if you choose GA 1 or GA 10. Ennis will be the VISITING team tonight.

If you are headed to the game tonight, please review the attached parking map for The Star. If you can't make it to the game, tune in on Channel 21 or listen in on 106.9 The Ranch. Go Lions!!

Yesterday EHS Senior Sarah Bell signed her National Letter of Intent to play soccer at NCAA Division III school LeTourneau University in Longview, Texas. Sarah is a four-year starter for the Ennis Lady Lions Soccer team where she plays goalkeeper. Outside of school, she plays for the Solar Soccer Club. Sarah is a student of outstanding character and is an outstanding student ranking in the top 10 in her class.

Congratulations, Sarah! #WeAreEnnis

shared_text:
Community Independent School District
November 5, 2019 at 10:30 PM Â·

(Tuesday, November 5, 2019) Tonight we were devastated to learn of a tragic car accident involving multiple students from Community ISD. We are grateful to the first responders on the scene. As they continue to investigate CISD will refrain from making any additional comment out of respect for the families. Our thoughts and prayers are with these families and with the entire Brave Nation as we grieve together. Counselors will be available to help support students and staff first thing in the morning.

Items not allowed inside the Corsicana ISD stadium include weapons, alcohol, umbrellas, animals, coolers, balloons, food, and drinks.

shared_text:
Ennis ISD Police Department
October 29, 2019 at 9:13 PM Â·

***FRIDAY NIGHT FOOTBALL ANNOUNCEMENT***

We are expecting a huge crowd for this anticipated game versus Corsicana, so here is some important information that has been shared with us in regards to Fridayâ€™s game. Please look carefully at the map below for parking information.

The YELLOW BOX on the map is designated for buses ONLY. Please do not park in this area!

The WHITE BOXES on the map are for visitor parking. We are confident that this area will fill up quick causing the overflow parking area to be used. The BLACK BOXES on the map are for the overflow parking. If you are using the overflow parking, please use the crosswalk and follow the path to the stadium entrance.

Corsicana ISD has a bag check policy as well. There will be a CISD employee at all entrances checking bags for any prohibited items. Please understand that this is done strictly for security reasons. Take a look at the image below to better understand what items are not allowed in the stadium.

Please share this post to help us get the word out!

GO LIONS!!!!
